OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDelay cap on social care   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcosts, councils warn       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, England's county councils have urged   
OL,6, the government to delay its social care
OL,7, reforms, warning of serious staffing   
OL,8, and financial pressures on services.   
OL,10,FChanges designed to help people cover  
OL,11,Ftheir personal care costs are due to   
OL,12,Fcome into effect in October 2023.      
OL,14,FThe changes include a more generous    
OL,15,Fmeans-test and a lifetime cap on care  
OL,16,Fcosts of #86,000.                      
OL,18,FBut councils say adult care services   
OL,19,Fcould deteriorate if the rollout of    
OL,20,Freforms is not delayed for a year.     
